On Thu, 13 Jun 1996, Miroslav Silovic wrote:
&gt; Users wouldn't
&gt; notice that unless the RAM cache fills up with modified objects, in
&gt; which case the game would pause further till the filesystem backup is
&gt; done).

Actually, I'd still like to have a special case where you can specify a 
backup cache size different (larger) from the run-time cache size.  I'd 
be a simple thing to let the cache grow, and then when you receive the 
signal that its done copying and you can write again reduce the cache 
back down to its original size and set the width/depth back to normal..

-Brandon
